t\nhigher disk surface densities in turn require lower viscosities to build the\nchain. Our results show that well characterized observed planetary systems hold\ninformation about their formation conditions in the protoplanetary disks and\nthat it is possible to extract this information, namely the initial disk\nsurface density and viscosity, helping to constrain planet formation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 26 Oct 2021 16:31:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-11"}
