clude that a\ndeep-learning method using a combination of a Bayesian Neural Network and a\nMixture Density Network offers the most accurate photometric redshifts for the\ncurrent test sample. It achieves single-point photometric redshifts with\nscatter ($\\sigma_\\text{NMAD}$) of 0.023, normalized bias of -0.001, and outlier\nfraction of 0.64% for galaxies with r-auto magnitudes between 16 and 21.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 26 Oct 2021 17:55:37 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 1 Feb 2022 21:28:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-03"}
