. Galaxies that host BH mergers\nare unbiased tracers of the overall $M_{\\rm BH} - M_{*}$ relation. Massive\n($>10^{11} M_{\\odot}$) galaxies have a high occupation number (>10) of BHs, and\nhence host the majority of BH mergers.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 27 Oct 2021 04:14:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 20 Mar 2022 17:44:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-22"}
