ght curves if the transit is fully covered,\nincluding out-of-transit data toward both sides, in some cases down to 0.7 ppt\ndepth. For Kepler-94b, Kepler-63b, and K2-100b, we were able to verify the\nephemeris. In the case of K2-138c with a 0.6 ppt deep transit, we were able to\nrefine it, and in the case of K2-138e, we ruled out the transit in the time\ninterval of more than +-1.5 sigma of its current literature ephemeris.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 27 Oct 2021 10:51:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-19"}
